## en-US (English)

**PRIVACY POLICY - Organizee**
Last updated: May 1, 2026
Developer: VandreApps

### ABOUT THE DEVELOPER

VandreApps is an independent developer, operating as an individual, without affiliation to any company or corporate organization. All development, maintenance, and support of the Organizee application are performed autonomously and individually.

---

### 1. INTRODUCTION

This Privacy Policy contains information about the collection, use, storage, processing, and protection of personal data of users of the Organizee application, developed by VandreApps, with the purpose of demonstrating absolute transparency on the subject and clarifying to all interested parties about the types of data that are collected and the reasons for the collection.

---

### 2. DATA STORAGE

**By default — Local Storage:**
All data created and managed by the user within the application (such as inventory information, products, categories, transactions, custom settings, and other registered information) are stored exclusively on the user's device and are **not** sent to the developer's external servers.

The developer does not have access to, does not collect, and does not store this personal data on any proprietary server **when the cloud sharing feature is not enabled**.

**Cloud Sharing (optional — Premium feature):**
The application offers, as an optional paid feature, the ability to sync inventory between devices through Firebase (Google). When activating this feature:

- The shared warehouse data (products, quantities, transactions, photos) is sent to and stored on Firebase (Google) servers.
- Access is restricted to the user(s) who have the access code to the shared warehouse.
- The developer, as Firebase administrator, may technically have access to cloud-stored data. However, they commit to never accessing, using, or sharing the content of users' data, except when required by law.
- The user can delete cloud data at any time through the application itself.
- Data is stored in Firebase Firestore and Firebase Storage, according to Google/Firebase privacy policies.

**Usage Analytics:**
Although the created data remains local (or in the cloud if the feature is enabled), the application records usage events (such as screens visited and features accessed) through Firebase Analytics for application improvement purposes. No personal content created by the user is sent in this process.

---

### 3. INFORMATION COLLECTED BY THIRD PARTIES

The application uses third-party services that may automatically collect information for analysis, advertising, and purchase processing purposes. The data collected includes:

**3.1. Data Collected**
- Device identification: model, operating system, application version, and unique identifiers
- Usage information: access frequency, features used, session time
- Advertising information: number of impressions, clicks, and interactions with ads
- Transaction data: information about in-app purchases (when applicable)
- Navigation events: screens viewed, features accessed, time on each functionality
- User actions: buttons clicked, forms accessed (without content), features used
- Engagement metrics: frequency of use of each feature, navigation sequence
- **Inventory data (only if the cloud sharing feature is active):** products, quantities, transactions, and photos are stored in Firebase

**3.2. Third-Party Services Used**
- Google Services and AdMob: ad display
- Firebase Analytics: application usage and performance analysis
- Firebase Firestore and Firebase Storage: cloud data storage (only for users with active sharing)
- RevenueCat: subscription and purchase management
- Google Play Store: distribution and in-app purchase management

**3.3. Events Tracked by Firebase Analytics**
The application records the following types of events for usage analysis:

- Accessed screens: record of which screens were viewed
- Features used: which functionalities were triggered
- User actions: interactions with buttons, menus, and interface elements
- Usage time: session duration and time on each functionality
- Navigation flow: sequence of screens visited

> **Important:** The content entered by the user (product names, quantities, values, descriptions, notes, and any registered data) is **NOT** sent to Analytics. Only usage and navigation metrics are collected, without personal identification.

---

### 4. PURPOSE OF DATA USE

The information collected by third-party services is used to:

- **Ad display:** improve the relevance of ads displayed to users through Google AdMob
- **Statistical analysis:** understand which features are most used to implement improvements
- **Feature tracking:** identify which functionalities are most accessed to prioritize improvements
- **Cross-device synchronization:** store and sync inventory data in the cloud (only with explicit user consent when activating the feature)
- **Purchase processing:** manage subscriptions and in-app purchases
- **Performance improvement:** identify and fix technical issues
- **Experience personalization:** adapt the application to user preferences

---

### 5. LEGAL BASIS FOR DATA PROCESSING

The processing of personal data is carried out based on the following legal bases:

- User consent when using the application and accepting this policy
- **Explicit consent** when voluntarily enabling the cloud sharing feature
- Legitimate interest for application improvements and statistical analysis
- Contract execution for purchase and subscription processing

---

### 6. DATA SHARING

The developer does not share, sell, or rent users' personal data. The only information shared is:

1. That automatically collected by the mentioned third-party services, according to their respective privacy policies.
2. **Shared warehouse data**, sent by the user to Firebase when voluntarily enabling the cloud synchronization feature.

The developer does not have direct access to individual user data but receives aggregated and anonymized reports from Firebase Analytics about general application usage.

**6.1. International Data Transfer**
The third-party services used (Google, RevenueCat) may transfer data to servers located outside Brazil, following their own privacy and data protection policies.

---

### 7. DATA SECURITY

- Data stored locally on the device is the user's responsibility in terms of physical device security.
- Data stored in the cloud (when the feature is active) is protected by Firebase/Google security measures, with access restricted by warehouse access code.
- The developer implements security rules in Firebase (Firestore Security Rules and Storage Rules) to restrict access to authorized users.

**Limitation of Liability for Security:**
The developer has made reasonable efforts to protect user data, including implementing access rules in Firebase, in-transit encryption (TLS) provided by Google's infrastructure, and access control via warehouse code. However, this is an independently developed project, maintained by a single person, without a dedicated security team or professional third-party security audit. Therefore, **absolute protection cannot be guaranteed** against failures, leaks, or unauthorized access resulting from: (i) vulnerabilities in third-party services such as Firebase/Google; (ii) compromised devices; (iii) disclosure of the access code by the user themselves to third parties; (iv) unidentified vulnerabilities in the application code.

If you require a higher level of security — such as end-to-end encryption, certified security auditing, or compliance with standards such as ISO 27001, SOC 2, HIPAA, or similar — we recommend evaluating specialized enterprise solutions that offer formal security guarantees compatible with those requirements.

The user is solely responsible for managing who receives access to their shared warehouse code. Under no circumstances shall the developer be held liable for damages resulting from security events beyond their direct control.

---

### 8. DATA RETENTION

- **Local data:** remains on the user's device until the application is uninstalled or data is manually deleted.
- **Cloud data:** remains on Firebase servers while the user keeps the feature active. The user can delete cloud data at any time through the application. Inactive warehouses may be automatically removed after a period of inactivity, as informed in the application.
- **Third-party data:** retained according to each service's policies (generally between 2 and 14 months for analytical data).

---

### 9. USER RIGHTS OVER CLOUD DATA

When using the cloud sharing feature, the user has the right to:

- **Access** their data at any time through the application
- **Delete** all cloud data through the application
- **Disable** cloud sharing at any time
- **Export** data via ZIP backup through the application

---

### 10. PERSONALIZED ADVERTISING AND OPT-OUT

You can disable personalized ads through your device settings or by accessing:

- Google Ads Settings: https://adssettings.google.com/
- Network Advertising Initiative: https://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/

> **Note:** Disabling personalized ads does not prevent ad display, but they will be less relevant to your interests.

---

### 11. THIRD-PARTY SERVICE PRIVACY POLICIES

- Google Services and AdMob: https://policies.google.com/privacy
- Firebase Analytics and Firestore: https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy
- RevenueCat: https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy
- Google Play Store: https://play.google.com/about/privacy-security-deceptive-behavior/

---

### 12. DEVELOPER DECLARATION

The developer VandreApps declares that:

- Does not collect, store, or process users' personal data on proprietary servers
- **When the cloud sharing feature is disabled:** all data created by the user remains stored locally on the device
- **When the cloud sharing feature is active:** the shared warehouse data is stored in Firebase (Google), with restricted access and under user control
- Only the third-party services mentioned in this policy have access to analytical and advertising data
- The application does not request access to camera, microphone, contacts, photo gallery, or location, except when explicitly necessary for specific functionalities (e.g., barcode scanning, adding product photos) and always with prior user permission
- The content of data entered by the user (names, values, quantities, descriptions) is never sent to Firebase Analytics services

---

### 13. COOKIES AND TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES

The application uses tracking technologies through the mentioned third-party services (Firebase Analytics, AdMob) to collect information about application usage. These technologies include:

- **Device identifiers:** to recognize the device across different sessions
- **Session tokens:** to track usage duration and frequency
- **Tracking pixels:** to measure interactions with ads

These technologies are managed by the respective third-party services according to their policies.

---

By using the Organizee application, you agree to this Privacy Policy and the data processing described herein.
